<TEXT>
one in three japanese favor moving the capital out 
of tokyo because the city of 116 million is so crowded a 
government poll released today indicates 
the poll conducted by the prime ministers office found 326 
percent of respondents to favor relocation with 17 percent opposed 
another 343 percent were undecided and 161 percent had no answer 
those favoring relocation say it is necessary to correct 
overconcentration of the population and solve housing and 
transportation problems those opposed say businesses should instead 
be distributed to places other than tokyo 
nearly 10 percent of japans people live in tokyo 
the office said it questioned 10000 people age 20 and older at 
random in december 
</TEXT>
