<TEXT>
a fear of flying has cost a former british member 
of the european parliament 1240 the fine imposed by a court 
because he refused to fasten his airplane seat belt 
richard cottrell 45 was arrested at heathrow airport on may 24 
after arriving from frankfurt on a lufthansa flight 
an airline spokeswoman said at the time that cottrell had refused 
to fasten his seat belt as the flight approached london and 
attempted to continue the argument in the cockpit with the captain 
cottrell a conservative was fined monday after pleading guilty 
to acting in a manner likely to endanger an aircraft or the people 
aboard 
at the magistrates court hearing the defense said cottrells 
fear of flying was the reason he refused to fasten his seat belt 
cottrell went to the cockpit door and told the pilot i am a 
member of parliament after he was told international regulations 
required all passengers to wear seat belts the court was told 
prosecutor neville casselmann said cottrell remained at the 
cockpit until the pilot shouted out we are landing 
he returned to his seat about two minutes before the landing 
defense attorney patrick darby said his client for some 
considerable time had a largescale phobia of flying it arose out 
of an incident 15 years ago when he was a passenger in a light 
aircraft forced to make an emergency landing he was badly shaken up 
by it 
he added that his client always sits near the emergency exits 
and never fastens his seat belt 
in this months european parliament elections cottrell lost the 
bristol western england seat he had held for 10 years 
</TEXT>
