and hopefully the dust will be cleared from the books jackson 
told reporters that day he was referring to the reagan 
administrations civil rights record which was roundly criticized 
by black leaders 
as he did after the meeting with jackson thornburgh has 
repeatedly expressed commitment to the full enforcement of civl 
rights laws and the full enjoyment of equal opportunity by all 
of its citizens 
but the attorney general has conceded he may have differences 
with civil rights leaders about achieving those goals 
