<TEXT>
amending the constitution is a difficult 
process thousands of amendments have been proposed but in more 
than 200 years only 26 have been ratified 
there are two ways to amend the constitution one initiated by 
congress and one by the state legislatures 
under the constitutions article v a proposed amendment 
originating in congress must be approved by twothirds votes in both 
houses it then must be approved by 38 state legislatures 
twothirds of the state legislatures may call for a 
constitutional convention any amendment approved by that convention 
must then be ratified by threefourths of the states 
</TEXT>
