<TEXT>
kraft has begun sending out 250 checks as 
consolation prizes for wouldbe winners of a 17000 van offered in 
the companys botched ready to roll contest officials said 
tuesday 
the food company based in this northwest chicago suburb had 
planned to give away only one van in the game but a printing error 
in newspaper inserts distributed june 11 created hundreds perhaps 
thousands of winning combinations with matching pieces in packages 
of kraft singles cheese 
the firm nullified the contest june 12 but offered the 250 to 
those holding game pieces that indicated they had won the van 
we hope that the actions were taking will show consumers how 
much we appreciate their understanding and patience during this 
situation said kathy knuth a spokeswoman for kraft usa 
the checks from the food company are accompanied by letters 
saying that the company is sorry for any confusion or 
disappointment the flawed game may have caused 
the grand prize in the game offered only in chicago and houston 
areas was a 1990 dodge caravan le worth 17000 
officials of kraft usa a division of kraft general foods which 
is part of philip morris cos inc of new york city have so far 
not specified how many people mailed in matching game pieces for the 
van and other prizes offered 
that information isnt available right now ms knuth said 
tuesday 
after the error was discovered and the game canceled kraft 
officials announced a modified contest 
claimants were required to have mailed their pieces by midnight 
june 16 to qualify for cash and a july 14 drawing for four vans and 
other prizes the company also announced plans to send 250 checks 
to van claimants 
jerry ohearn 48 of suburban brookfield got his check in the 
mail monday just 10 days after he sent in his game pieces 
those kraft people just made a big flub out of the whole 
deal said ohearn 
but he said he does not intend to participate in classaction 
lawsuits against the company at least two such lawsuits were filed 
earlier this month with plaintiffs seeking more than the 250 the 
company offered 
i can see how a mistake could happen said ohearn its 
pretty fair what theyve done 
in addition to the van kraft had originally planned to award 100 
bicycles 500 skateboards and 8000 packages of cheese 
ms knuth said that payments have also started going to wouldbe 
winners of those prizes 50 to bicycle winners 25 to skateboard 
winners and 5 to cheese winners she said she was unsure whether 
all checks had been mailed 
only one winner is allowed per household under company rules 
