<TEXT>
through marketing ingenuity incentives good 
design improved quality and sheer persistence automakers have 
managed to stretch their selling cycle long beyond its usual 
lifespan 
now they are faced with another situation with the delayed but 
inevitable end of their growth cycle appearing on the horizon can 
they manage to maintain their stock prices until the next upturn 
automaking is a cyclical industry meaning it has at least as 
many ups and downs as the economy itself the pattern is as distinct 
as in real estate a rising demand overproduction big inventories 
a downturn and a recovery 
its been a bit different this time amid intense competition 
the carmakers developed techniques to shift the production mix 
cars vs trucks for example offer discounts and belowmarket 
interest rates and finetune production 
in so doing they demonstrated that the cycle can indeed be 
stretched if only to a point now with indications it could snap 
july output may be at an annual rate of only 5 million cars lowest 
for any month since 1982 you might think the appeal of automaker 
stocks would fall but it might not 
with industry earnings heading for a secondhalf decline 
automotive stocks still remain in many portfolios one reason being 
that analysts believe the automakers might be able to do for their 
stocks what they did for their sales 
how do you keep stock prices up 
by using the money you earned in the good times to buy back your 
stocks as general motors and ford are doing thus tending to 
maintain the supplydemand ratio 
by maintaining dividends at a rate higher than most blue chips 
general motors current dividend yield is 66 percent fords 62 
percent and chryslers 48 percent 
by making operations more efficient thus buffering earnings to 
some degree against a sales downturn 
ford often is cited as the best example of improved operating 
efficiency moreover it chose to meet demand in the good days by 
expanding overtime rather than expanding plants it costs less to 
reduce overtime than to close a plant 
still another factor low priceearnings ratios conceivably 
could protect share prices gm sells for six times earnings ford 
four and chrysler five for the market as a whole the pe is in the 
double digits 
reflecting some of these considerations the value line 
investment survey offers these views of the big three automakers on 
the eve of a sales downturn 
general motors we look for negative quarterly matchups for the 
remainder of 89 and expect the fullyears earnings to decline by 
about 12 percent 
these shares have impressive total return potential for the 
three to fiveyear term in the meantime they provide an 
aboveaverage yield based on a secure payout 
ford we expect ford shares to keep pace with the market in the 
year ahead protected from most downside risk by a secure dividend 
that provides an attractive yield 
chrysler patient investors should keep this stock in mind 
although recent earnings comparisons suggest the stock is only 
likely to be an average performer in the year ahead we project 
sharply improved earnings for the company by 19921994 
if it turns out that way the major automakers may have succeeded 
not just in muting the ups and downs of the car market but of the 
stock market too 
