sec and the firm that places drexel under strict supervision for 
three years approval of the separate criminal settlement is pending 
before another judge 
once that happens phelan said we will go full blast 
the exchange has been talking to the sec and has been examining 
the secs proposed settlement torrenzano said 
in 1985 the nyse fined ef hutton amp co 400000 and censured 
its president and chief financial officer for failing to supervise 
the firm properly after hutton pleaded guilty to federal mail and 
wire fraud charges in a wideranging checkkiting scheme 
